euro zone economy to pick up faster this year : ecb official
xinhua news agency , brussels , march 20 ( reporter wang xingqiao ) dr. yassin , chief economist of the european central bank , said here on the 20th that the euro zone 's economy has walked out of the trough and will start to pick up more rapidly this year .
yassin made the remarks at a hearing held by the european parliament in brussels .
he said the latest data show that the euro zone economy is picking up slowly at the beginning of this year , and it is expected that the speed of economic recovery will accelerate within this year .
it is estimated that the euro zone 's economic growth this year will reach the level of 2% to 2.5% .
in his view , the recovery of the euro zone 's economy is mainly due to the growth of consumer spending and the current low level of stock of goods in the euro zone .
on inflation , yassin said that the overall inflation rate in the euro zone is falling , and there is no indication that there will be any risk of price instability in the medium term .
talking about the current energy situation in the world , yassin said that the recent rise in oil prices in the world market has caused concern among economic policymakers around the world , and the impact of rising oil prices on long - term economic trends should not be underestimated .
first case of drug trafficking detected in hk
xinhua news agency , hong kong , march 21 , the hong kong police have recently discovered people using the internet to smuggle drugs on the internet .
the narcotics division of the hong kong police pointed out that this is the first time that the hong kong police have discovered such a discovery and it should arouse serious attention .
according to the hong kong police , in the past year there have been a number of cases in which hong kong people used the internet to make payment by credit cards and buy ecstasy .
drug traffickers bought drugs in thailand and sent them to drug addicts in hong kong .
the chief superintendent of the narcotics bureau of the hong kong police force , mr ip lau - chuen , said that several cases reported last year were mainly the use of credit cards to place orders on the internet .
the hong kong police are cooperating with the relevant disciplined forces to crack down on this new crime .
at the recent conference on transnational organised crime held in hong kong , a responsible person of the united nations international narcotics commission pointed out that drug trafficking on the internet would be a new challenge for law enforcement agencies in the future .
last year , the security bureau of the hong kong special administrative region completed consultation on computer crime and will amend the law to crack down on any acts of using computers to commit crimes .
african college students urge not to make africa the fringe of new technology
xinhua news agency , abidjan , march 21 ( reporter song nan ) at the second forum of african higher learning institutions , which opened on the 21st , university students attending the forum called on african youths to actively use high technology in information and communications to cope with the challenge of economic globalization and not to let the african continent become a " fringe region " of new technology .
the chairman of the meeting said in his speech : high technology has promoted the development of countries in asia , europe , and the united states .
the arrival of the new century has brought many opportunities and challenges to the african continent . african young people should strive to master new and high technologies and make their due contributions to africa 's better tomorrow .
the theme of this year 's forum of african institutions of higher learning is : " new technology , information and exchanges will bring more opportunities for training african people . "
during the three - day conference , experts from a dozen institutions of higher learning and enterprises in africa will discuss such special topics as " africa 's future and new technological challenges , " " cultural diversity and economic development , " and " the opportunities and prospects brought about by e - commerce for africa . "
a major campus culture exhibition will also be held during the conference period .
indonesia opposes foreign troops deployment
xinhua news agency , jakarta , march 22 ( reporter mak tong - yuan ) the indonesian foreign ministry issued a press communique on the 22 nd , reiterating its opposition to foreign troops entering this island nation .
the indonesian ministry of foreign affairs reiterated this stance in response to a report carried by today 's usa today that the united states intends to send troops to indonesia to help crack down on " al - qaeda " members fleeing from afghanistan .
the us government has never formally raised the above request to the indonesian government , which can be confirmed by the white house and the defense department later denying .
the communique reiterated that indonesia is pursuing an independent foreign policy and that indonesia has carried out close and beneficial cooperation with the united states and other countries in fighting terrorism . the indonesian government is willing to continue to strengthen cooperation in this regard .
ukraine condemns u.s. for interfering in its internal affairs
xinhua news agency report of march 22nd from kiev ( by staff reporter zhang zhiqiang ) - ukraine president kuchma gave a speech to the press on the 22nd on us house of representatives interfering in ukraine 's internal affairs , saying that the resolution of the us house of representatives was without precedent and " puzzling " .
the u.s. house of representatives on tuesday passed a resolution calling on ukraine to guarantee a transparent , free and fair election on the 31 st of this month .
the resolution also pointed out that the ukrainian government must earnestly implement its new parliamentary election law , and the results of the election should indicate whether ukraine will continue to carry out democratic reform .
kuchma indicated : " the ukrainian nation is not a soccer that can be set up at will . the ukrainian people should have their own dignity . "
kuchma also expressed his thanks for the letter to the u.s. congress .
luciano said in his letter , " see what you have done .
i first studied at home and then taught others . "
on the same day , ukrainian communist party leader simon said that the us action was a gross interference in ukraine 's internal affairs and a threat to ukraine 's independence .
the leader of ukraine 's united social democratic party , gujinko , said that the one - sided appraisal of ukraine 's election activities by the us house of representatives resolution would lead to polarization of ukraine 's political forces .
a spokesman for the ukrainian foreign ministry said today that the election of representatives of ukraine 's supreme legislative body and local legislative body is purely a matter for the ukrainian people .
in the final stage of ukraine 's parliamentary election activities , it is hoped that all countries will show a prudent attitude and observe the norms of international law such as non - interference in internal affairs .
arab states oppose u.s. attack on iraq
xinhua news agency , lagos , march 23 , according to a report in riyadh on the 23rd , lebanese president lahoud said in an interview with the newspaper that although the arab summit has not yet opened , they have taken a unanimous stand on the iraq issue to oppose us attacks on iraq .
lahoud pointed out that no arab country agrees that the united states or its allies strike at any arab country without any legitimate reason , and the united states must understand the consequences of such attacks , regardless of the excuse or under whatever cover of the attacks .
lahoud believes that cracking down on terrorism or " axis of evil " is an attractive pretext that affects western opinion , but criminal activities should not be carried out under such pretexts .
he also urged the united states not to pursue double standards , that is , cracking down on terrorism in one region but ignoring the national terrorism action taken by israel in another region .
