indonesian parliament speaker faces trial in court
xinhua news agency , beijing , march 25 , according to information received here , indonesian parliament speaker akbar tanjung appeared at a jakarta court on the 25th for charges of corruption and redemption .
tanjung was accused of being responsible for the illegal embezzlement of eight million dollars worth of relief funds from the indonesian state food and food department .
this batch of funds was reportedly used to finance the campaign activities of the party of professional groups headed by akbar tanjung in 1999 .
the relief funds were originally used for some poor families hit by the financial crisis , but investigators of the case found that the funds were not in the hands of these families .
tanjung , however , has denied the allegation .
analysts believe that regardless of the outcome of the trial , this incident may weaken tanjung 's hope of being elected indonesian president .
" forging ahead " postponed to the sky due to mechanical failure
xinhua news agency , washington , march 25 , the us national space agency said on the 25th that due to technical problems in the mechanical hands of canada made in the international space station , the launch of the " forging ahead " space shuttle will be postponed from may 6 to may 31 .
it is reported that the " forging ahead " will then take seven astronauts to the international space station for an 11 - day space flight .
the seven people include astronauts from france and russia .
a spokesperson for the us national space agency said that space station staff can take full advantage of this period to remove the trouble , but the postponement means that they still have to patiently stay for more than three weeks , waiting for the replacement of pelosi and two other russian astronauts in the united states .
phillip perry from france is the first non - russian european astronaut to fly to the space station . he will walk twice at the start of his mission .
shell to invest 5 billion us dollars in china in three years
xinhua news agency , beijing , march 26 ( reporter qian chunxian ) wu zpei , chairman of the board of the shell group , said recently that the total investment of shell in china will reach 5 billion us dollars by 2005 .
shell 's investment in china has reached 1.6 billion us dollars and its planned investment in china will reach 5 billion us dollars in 2005 , he said .
shell is currently negotiating with china on a number of cooperative projects .
among which , 500 gas station joint venture projects with china petrochemical group corporation are expected to be launched this year .
he said shell has had business contacts with china for more than 100 years .
for shell , the chinese market has huge potential and is an important part of its global strategy .
as the economy develops , china 's demand for energy is expected to double by 2020 , and by that time china 's energy consumption will account for 16 percent of the world 's total .
china is facing serious energy challenges , while diversification of energy sources is very important to energy security and environmental protection , and shell will play an important role in this process .
xinhua news agency , united nations , march 26 ( reporter gu zhenqiu ) a un security council delegation will visit congo ( kinshasa ) on april 27 and other african countries involved in the conflicts in order to inject new vitality into the peace process in drc , un spokesman announced on the 26th .
the spokesman said : the french permanent representative to the united nations , levitte , will lead the delegation , consisting of representatives from 15 member countries of the security council .
the main purpose of the visit is to hold dialogue with the leaders of all parties involved in the conflicts in the drc in order to promote their adherence to the peace accord signed in lusaka , capital of zambia in 1999 .
this is the third time since may 2000 that the security council has sent a delegation to visit the great lakes region of africa .
sri lanka to hold peace talks with tigers
xinhua news agency , colombo , march 27 ( reporter zhang yadong ) the sri lankan government announced on the 27 th that it plans to hold peace talks with the rebel tamil tiger liberation organization in early may with a view to ending its nearly 20 - year - old bloody national conflict in the country .
speaking at a press conference on the same day , sri lanka 's minister of justice , the constitution , ethnic affairs and the national physical culture said that the sri lankan government and the tigers have agreed to hold peace talks as soon as possible , and the government hopes the talks can be held in the first week of may .
he said : the initial talks will mainly make preparations for entering into substantive talks .
the slovak government has not yet formally announced the venue of the talks , but there are reports that the peace talks between the two sides will be held in thailand .
pelosi said that the government intends to hold talks with the tigers in a certain asian country and has made relevant preparations for the talks .
according to another report , after being in exile in london for three years , balassin , the chief negotiator of the ltte group that returned to the northern part of sri lanka on the 25th , and the leader of the organization , puhrabachlan , recently held talks with norwegian special envoy solheim and norwegian ambassador to sri lanka in the northern part of sri lanka .
after the talks , the tigers agreed to resume peace talks with the government when the situation in the region under their control was returning to normal . however , they insisted that the government lift the ban on them before the peace talks .
in february this year , the sri lankan government signed a permanent ceasefire agreement with the tigers , laying a foundation for the two sides to start talks .
the net profit of china unicom rose by nearly 38% last year
xinhua news agency , hong kong , march 27 ( reporter li kai ) the china unicom stocks limited , a listed company in hong kong , announced here today that in 2001 , china unicom had achieved good results in all fields of its business , with a total turnover of 293.93 billion yuan rmb , achieving net profit of 44.57 billion yuan rmb , an increase of nearly 38% over the previous year .
as one of china 's comprehensive telecommunications operators , china united telecommunications corporation provides various telecommunications services , including mobile telecommunications , international and domestic long - distance telecommunications , data , internet , and paging services .
china united telecommunications corporation announced that last year the total number of long - distance telephone calls and calls made by the company for circuits exchanges and calls reached 64.1 billion minutes , an increase of 5.9 times over the previous year , and its market share increased to 7.7 percent from 1.3 percent in 2000 . the total number of international communications continued for the whole year increased 3.4 times over the previous year .
yang xianzu , chief executive officer of china unicom , said that the company would continue to speed up the development of mobile communications business this year and adopt a dissolute strategy to ensure the coordinated development of the company 's mobile telecommunications business and enable the company 's mobile phone users to continue to increase significantly .
central bank , japan sign currency swap agreement
xinhua news agency , tokyo , march 28 ( reporter wang yan ) dai xianglong , governor of the people 's bank of china , and masaru hayami , governor of the bank of japan , signed a bilateral currency exchange agreement on the 28 th in tokyo .
according to the agreement , when necessary , the people 's bank of china and the bank of japan can provide each other with currency exchange arrangements amounting to 3 billion us dollars in order to help maintain the stability of the financial market .
the signing of the currency exchange agreement between china and japan shows that the cooperation between the central banks of china and japan has been further strengthened .
the agreement is the second bilateral currency swap agreement signed between the people 's bank of china and the bank of thailand in december 2001 .
in the future , china will also sign currency exchange agreements with south korea and other countries .
dai xianglong said : china will actively participate in asian financial cooperation , and is willing to join hands with other asian countries and regions in making their own contributions to regional economic and financial stability and to guarding against risks .
chinese ambassador to japan wu dawei attended the signing ceremony for the agreement between the people 's bank of china and the bank of japan on currency exchange .
afghan quake victims rebuild homes
xinhua news agency , kabul , march 28 ( reporter pan yunzhao ) just three days after the earthquake , earthquake victims in northern afghanistan 's bagram province have started rebuilding their homes .
a central group formed by the afghan interim government , united nations agencies and non - governmental organizations was conducting an inspection and assessment of the earthquake - stricken area on the 28th . it was found that disaster victims were working on rebuilding their own houses , and some of them also used relief supplies provided by relief agencies .
she said that based on this situation , the un relief organizations have already begun to consider the issue of assisting the victims to rebuild their homes .
currently , relief agencies have a large amount of relief supplies in the earthquake - stricken area and are distributing them to the victims through the land and the air .
several tens of thousands of people were left homeless by a strong earthquake that hit nahlin and bolshehr areas in afghanistan 's bagdad on thursday , reports reaching here said .
japan freeze humanitarian aid to russia
xinhua news agency , tokyo , march 29 , japanese foreign minister yoriko kawaguchi announced on the 29 th that japan will temporarily freeze providing humanitarian aid to russia until the international committee responsible for the aid projects is rectified .
kawaguchi said that apart from maintaining the committee 's manpower expenditure and a technical cooperation project that japan is currently providing to russia , the japanese government will control the funding for the committee until it can rectify the situation .
the decision was made in response to the recent remarks made by japanese finance minister masajuro shiokawa .
masajuro shiokawa recently told the cabinet members that in view of the deteriorating fiscal situation in japan , the cabinet members should ensure that every item of funds from the government can be put to good use .
it has been learned that after deputy chief cabinet secretary suzuki exposed the improper pressure exerted by the ministry of foreign affairs on the application procedures for russian aid projects , the committee was accused of dereliction of duty by outsiders and was not transparent about the whereabouts of funds .
eu to discuss china 's temporary safeguard for steel imports
xinhua news agency , beijing , march 29 ( reporter : wu yuming ) shi guangsheng , minister of foreign trade and economic cooperation , said here today that the eu has responded explicitly to china 's concern about the eu 's temporary safeguard measures on some imported steel . he said that the eu would hold consultations with china as soon as possible and would make special arrangements for china as a developing country to properly solve this problem .
shi guangsheng today answered reporters ' questions at a national work conference on foreign economic relations and trade law .
he said : the more fierce a steel trade war becomes , the root cause of which is the united states .
at present , all parties concerned are making accusations against the united states ' " steel case " and bilateral consultations . some even proposed resolving the case through the wto dispute settlement mechanism .
on 27 march , after the eu decided to implement temporary safeguard measures for 15 kinds of imported steel from various countries , the chinese side responded in good time . shi guangsheng immediately wrote to eu trade commissioner pascal lamy , expressing deep concern over this and proposing bilateral negotiations with the eu .
seven killed in train crash in liaoning
xinhua news agency , shenyang , march 30 ( reporter wang jun ) at 1413 on march 29 , a train - to - car collision occurred in jincheng , liaoning province , killing seven people and seriously injuring three .
according to the safety inspection office of the shenyang railway bureau , a four - wheel agricultural vehicle collided with a train traveling from jinzhou to chengde at the railway crossing between lijiagou and zhou jiatun in yizhou county .
at that time , apart from 50 bags of fertilizer and seeds on the car , they carried 14 people in violation of regulations .
when the collision occurred , four people jumped into the train and escaped without injury . the other 10 people either died or were injured . the railway pole at daokou was damaged . the train train train was damaged to a certain extent .
after the accident , leaders of the ministry of railways , the shenyang railway bureau , the jincheng city , and the local government rushed to the scene to deal with the aftermath of the accident .
the council of the arab league held an emergency meeting at the arab league headquarters on the same day to discuss the palestinian situation .
representatives of 22 arab league representatives attended the meeting .
speaking at a press conference held after the meeting , moussa said israel 's refusal of peace is clear about the escalation of palestinian military operations .
what is happening now is the continuation of israeli military occupation of palestine and the palestinian people will continue to resist israeli aggression .
he said : " as long as israel occupies the palestinian territories , the resistance of the palestinian people will continue day by day as long as israeli tanks and soldiers exist in the palestinian territories . "
