by 2005 china 's telecommunications market will exceed 1 trillion yuan
xinhua news agency , shanghai , april 6 ( reporter feng yizhi ) an official from the ministry of information industry , who is attending a sino - russian symposium on information and communication here , revealed that by 2005 , the total scale of china 's telecommunications market will reach 1050 billion yuan , an increase of 2.5 times over 2000 .
it is estimated that during the 10th five - year plan period ( 2001 - 2005 ) , the number of telephone subscribers in china will increase at an average annual rate of about 26 percent . the central and eastern regions will be 24 percent , the central regions 26 percent , and the western regions 30 percent .
by 2005 , the number of telephone subscribers nationwide will reach 500 million and the popularization rate will be about 40 percent .
mobile telephone users in china will expand to ordinary consumers and expand from simple news services to data exchange , medium - and high - speed multimedia and high - speed multimedia businesses .
internet business will continue to be the fastest growing business of china 's telecommunications industry . the contents of demand will expand from a narrow band to a broadband business . the types of subscription service will develop into a high - speed interactive business . users will expand from large and medium - sized cities to central cities and towns .
during the 10th five - year plan period , the annual average growth rate of china 's digital and multimedia internet users will exceed 70 percent .
by 2005 , the number of internet users nationwide will reach 200 million .
