computer crime causes us losses of billions of dollars last year
xinhua news agency , washington , april 7 , computer crime and security investigations 2001 released on the 7 th by the united states show that increasingly arrogant computer crime inflicted billions of dollars on us companies and government departments last year , a big increase over 2000 .
cases of computer systems being attacked by computer viruses in various parts of the united states , of refusing to provide services , and of various security loopholes are common everywhere .
538 computer security experts from enterprises , government departments , and universities said that american companies and other institutions must pay a high price each year for computer crime .
although the exact amount of damage was not yet confirmed , 35 percent of the respondents admitted that they suffered losses with a total value exceeding $ 37.78 billion , a big increase from $ 26.56 billion in 2000 .
the report , jointly compiled by the computer security association of the united states and the fbi , did not provide any assessment of the losses suffered by individuals nationwide .
