xinhua news agency , moscow , april 22 ( reporter zhou liang ) georgian president shevardnadze denied a report on the united states ' refusal to help georgia reform its armed forces .
the president made the remarks at a press conference held in tbilisi , capital of southwest china 's sichuan province .
he said : neither the united states nor georgia has changed the agreement previously reached for us military experts to help georgia reform its armed forces , but there is still no specific date yet for us military experts to arrive in georgia .
he said that us military experts are now preparing to go to georgia , and they will come to georgia sooner or later .
he pointed out : the strengthening of cooperation between georgia and the united states in the military field is not aimed at russia .
according to the agreement reached between georgia and the united states , us military experts will assist georgia in training its troops of four battalions and one company this year .
