one quarter of the work report voted against or abandoned right to vote
npc deputies still dissatisfied with judicial reform
more than a quarter of china 's npc deputies voted against or abandoned the work reports of the supreme people 's court and the supreme people 's procuratorate yesterday , indicating that they are still not satisfied with the judicial reform achievements and the progress of the building of the rule of law .
however , among the 2,813 deputies attending the closing session of the fifth session of the ninth national people 's congress [ npc ] at the great hall of the people , 2,742 people voted in favor of premier zhu rongji 's government work report . the approval rate was as high as 97.5 percent , about the same as last year .
all sides expect that zhu rongji , who has made public his intention to step down , will withdraw from the standing committee of the political bureau 's supreme decision - making body at the 16th cpc national congress to be held this autumn .
however , the result of the vote showed that zhu was not cold - shouldered by deputies to the national people 's congress because he would soon lose his power .
the 10 - and - a - half - day congress also voted 80.5 percent to approve the 2002 budget of 309.8 billion yuan ( about 6.8 billion singapore dollars ) .
the work report of the standing committee of the national people 's congress delivered by li peng encountered slightly more objections and abstentions .
the report of the npc standing committee yesterday received 2,577 votes in favor , 112 votes against , and 114 abstentions .
last year 's report received 2,582 votes in favor , 85 votes against , and 122 abstentions .
although the reactions of npc deputies yesterday were slightly better than last year , as high as 28 percent and 27 percent of npc deputies voted against or cast their votes against the work reports of the supreme people 's court and the supreme people 's procuratorate .
xiao yang , president of the supreme people 's court , yesterday received 2,026 votes in favor of the work report , 528 votes against , and 259 abstentions .
last year , his report won 19,563 votes in favor , 530 votes against , and 306 abstentions .
han zhubin , procurator general of the supreme people 's procuratorate , yesterday received 2,044 votes in favor , 516 votes against , and 253 abstentions .
last year , his report won 1873 votes in favor , 584 votes against , and 332 abstentions .
since this year is the last session of the current npc and the next year 's session of the npc will be changed , the meeting that closed yesterday also voted through the " decision on the number of deputies to the 10th npc and the issue of election , " stipulating that the 10th npc should be elected before the end of january next year .
china accelerates changes in local party and government leaders
( hong kong report ) informed sources in beijing at the " two sessions " have revealed to ming pao that the change of local party and government leaders in china will be accelerated after the npc and cppcc sessions are over .
the central authorities have urged all localities to complete the work of electing new leaders by the end of june this year and the 17 provinces , municipalities , and autonomous regions that have not yet completed their readjustment to form new leading bodies .
the report says : in accordance with the cpc central committee 's criteria for appointment , members of provincial - level party and government leading bodies should generally have a college degree or above and a bachelor 's degree .
the central authorities have also laid down that the new secretary of the provincial party committee is under 59 years of age and the governor is under 56 .
in addition , to strengthen the cpc 's leadership over people 's congresses at all levels , after the local governments finish their term of office , all the chairmen of people 's congresses at all levels will be concurrently concurrently secretaries of their party committees at the same level .
the source pointed out : as of march last year , 62 party and government leaders in 31 provinces , autonomous regions , and municipalities across the country have carried out changes in their positions .
since last year , 14 provinces , including inner mongolia , jiangxi , hubei , hainan , yunnan , and qinghai , have completed the readjustment of the local party committees .
eleven provincial governors and mayors from shanghai , jiangxi , shandong , hunan , and yunnan have been transferred to posts in the provinces , municipalities , and autonomous regions .
