new york stocks move higher
( integrated ) us consumer confidence and industrial production went up in parallel , causing the wall street market to suffer a heavy fire , with the three major indexes rising at once , and the dow jones industrial and commercial index entering its fifth week more steadily .
investors believe that with the gradual us economic recovery , corporate profitability is also expected to pick up , with sales of chain stores in wal - mart , the largest chain store in the united states , and credit card issuers american express taking the lead in skyrocketing , the longest weekly increase since september 2000 .
the dow jones industrial and commercial index closed at 10,107.23 , up 90.09 or 0.9% when it closed on friday .
the us auto index reported 188.30 points , 14.16 points or 0.8 percent , while the broader range of standard ; poor 's 500 index reported 116.16 points , 13.12 points or 1.1 percent .
the dow jones industrial average rose slightly by 0.3% throughout the week , expanding to 5.8% this year .
the standard & poor 's 500 rose 0.2 percent , while the us 's automatic price index fell 3.2 percent , the first fall in three weeks .
the consumer confidence index for the united states , released by the university of michigan on friday , rose for the fifth time in six months , reaching the highest level of 15 months , indicating that the momentum of economic recovery is not small .
on the other hand , the u.s. industrial production index rose 0.4 percent in february , compared with expectations in the market and was the second rise in 17 months .
economists believe that these two data make the outline of economic recovery even clearer .
therefore , the future market trend may also be pushed toward a more optimistic field .
on the new york stock exchange , the proportion of stocks traded was 4 to 3 , with a turnover of 140 million shares .
meanwhile , the dow jones industrial average fell 6 to 5 .
in the british market , record firm eci may lay off employees , and biotech giant celtics may stop selling stocks , bringing the market an optimistic atmosphere and pushing the stock market up by 0.6% .
however , the second best - selling drug of gsk , a pharmaceutical manufacturer , may face competition from india 's rival , and the german bank 's reduction in the price expectation of the whole europe 's largest mobile phone dealer , has restricted the increase rate .
the london financial times closed friday at 5,292.70 , down 31.30 points .
dprk patrol boat intruded into rok territorial waters
( seoul , united states ) south korean officials said that a north korean patrol boat intruded into south korean territorial waters yesterday .
the south korean chief of staff said the patrol boat crossed the yellow sea border 1.5 km long and stayed 42 minutes before it was driven by a south korean warship .
it said that north korean patrol boats had accidentally intruded into south korean territorial waters while inspecting a cambodian cargo ship .
the sea borders between south and north korea are not clear , and yesterday 's crimes are the second of this year .
the rok accused the dprk of invading the western waters 12 times last year , but every time it is not serious .
a north korean warship sank in 1999 after a series of incursions into the sea , believed to have killed 30 north korean sailors .
on the other hand , intelligence sources said that the 25 north korean defectors stayed at a philippine army base yesterday before flying to south korea for asylum .
the refugees arrived at the manila airport on friday evening from beijing .
the relevant person said : " the documents they will visit south korea are being processed . "
the south korean foreign ministry said that these north korean people will fly to seoul on monday by a passenger plane from south korean airlines .
al - qaeda increases fund flow : us official
( washington d . c . ) according to us media reports , a us official who declined to be named said a few days ago that the financial activities of the al - qaeda , the international terrorist number one , have been added to the organization in recent weeks . this shows that some leaders of the al - qaeda are resuming their control over this organization and may possibly seek more financial assistance to attack us targets .
the official said that the communication link between the surviving qatar - based al - qaeda members was also on the rise as the fund flow of the al - qaeda increased .
information intercepted by us intelligence agencies shows that small shareholders qazi are liaising with taliban militants .
most of the communication and contact activities are concentrated in northwestern pakistan near the afghanistan border .
the official said these activities show that some of the well - known al - qaeda leaders are now recovering from the remaining control of the terrorists , but the us official declined to disclose the names of these people .
the anti - terrorism department of the us central intelligence agency ( cia ) said that there were many signs that the qazi group was being re - organized , with its large volume of communications carried out via the internet , and that there were also frequent fund exchanges .
canosano also said that evidence shows that the organizational leadership has begun to become active .
taiwan 's democratic progressive party legislator chen jinde and fishing groups visit beijing
chen jinde , legislative member of taiwan 's democratic progressive party , arrived in beijing yesterday with an inspection group formed by several fishing groups in taiwan .
chen jinde is the first dpp member to visit the mainland after chinese vice premier qian qichen made a speech to welcome the vast number of dpp members to visit the mainland in his proper capacity after marking the seventh anniversary of " jiang zemin 's eight - point proposal . "
chen jinde arrived in beijing yesterday for a 10 - day visit to hong kong on saturday .
chen jinde stressed that the purpose of his visit is simply to help fishermen in yilan district resolve the problem of shortage of fishing workers . therefore , he did not want to go to the mainland in his personal capacity . however , he revealed that the visit would meet with officials from the ministry of foreign trade and economic cooperation and relevant mainland nongovernmental organizations . he hoped that the beijing authorities would agree to resume the opening up of fishing operations to taiwan .
after the chinese mainland banned fishing workers from going to taiwan , there was a serious shortage of fisheries manpower in yulan prefecture . chen jinde decided to assist the fishing industry in beijing and taiwan in joining a delegation formed by the fishing associations in order to help the fishing industry in the mainland resume opening up to taiwan .
the delegation , headed by huang yongshou , director general of the taiwan provincial fishing association , left for beijing last thursday in the name of the " republic of china employment association for employees . "
serious sand storms occur in beijing
( beijing , new york ) chinese media said that another serious sand storm occurred in beijing yesterday .
although the government has invested huge sums in improving beijing 's environment and preventing the desert from approaching beijing , eliminating the major difficulties faced by beijing municipality , which has been plagued by frequent sandstorms each year , will still be the one that plans to host the 2008 olympic games .
china 's state meteorological bureau forecast that the first sandstorm this year hit beijing last friday , and the cold air from mongolia is expected to cover beijing in the sand and dust storms .
yang weixi , chief engineer of the desert control center of china 's forestry ministry , told beijing zhou bao : " i dare not say there will be no sandstorms in 2008 .
what we can do is to control human factors that cause sandstorms and prevent desertification in the environment . "
however , he said , natural factors such as wind , drought , and the great desert that exceed people 's ability to control have made china unable to avoid sandstorms in the short term .
the chinese government has pledged to invest 56.8 billion yuan ( 12.37 billion singapore dollars ) from 2002 to 2008 to prevent desertification and reduce sandstorms .
beijing alone will spend about 1 billion yuan ( about 220 million singapore dollars ) this year .
an expert from the chinese academy of forestry said : " the increase in financial appropriations will bring about a great improvement in the situation . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
after a survey conducted at the beginning of this year , chinese environmental experts warned : about one - third of china 's territory is now desert . this is mainly caused by human economic activities , such as over - grazing .
in the first six months of last year , 18 sandstorms occurred in beijing , all coming from inner mongolia , and 60 percent of the area in inner mongolia was desert , the report said .
at the just concluded npc session this month , deputies from shanghai , beijing , and inner mongolia urged the government to " build a green great wall ( formed by forests ) " to stop the attack of sandstorms .
according to a report by the shanghai star newspaper , xu shiyuan , vice president of the institute of geography in china , warned that if the government did not take emergency measures , sandstorms might even hit shanghai .
many cadres found to be involved in fake diploma fraud in china
( hong kong integrated news ) fake diploma in china was rampant in the pan - flood situation on the mainland . the guangdong provincial center for guidance on employment for college graduates recently assessed the academic credentials of 15 officials sent from a city in the chaoshan region . seven of them were confirmed as fake certificates only by the naked eyes .
according to reports in hong kong newspapers , since may last year , the center has received more than 3,500 post - graduation certificates , more than 800 certificates of various types have been issued , and the percentage of false certificates has reached 23% .
according to the report , the certificates were mostly issued by adult education and self - learning examinations , of which two thirds were forged on the street while the other one was issued by regular educational institutions .
the person in charge of the center also disclosed that since the institute was established and was undergoing institutional reform , the inspection and verification was generally conducted in government organs and enterprises and institutions . among these units , the proportion of false certificates of some units was very high . many owners of false certificates were working cadres .
with the approval of relevant departments of the ministry of education , the guangdong provincial employment guidance center for graduates of higher learning is the only organization in china to be authorized to conduct certification for higher education on a nationwide scale .
the responsible person also revealed that a state - owned bank of a prefectural - level city , out of consideration for selecting officials , sent 36 middle - ranking officials and backbone business personnel to appraise their diploma , and only six of them were true .
it is understood that along with the appraisal , quite a number of private enterprises have also asked for verification , and the main items identified are the new recruits and college students .
the ministry found that many of the college students ' certificates were fake goods .
last year , a large enterprise set up a branch in the pearl river delta region , recruiting a group of college students .
the boss sent more than 30 employees ' academic credentials for appraisal , and found that 10 of them were false .
in recent years , quite a number of non - local institutions in guangdong have set up separate teaching posts to attract students to join the scheme , but in order to attract them , they have resorted to fraud when recruiting students , claiming that they are issued with certificates of national recognition , and producing a batch of false certificates upon graduation .
25 asylum seekers arrive in seoul
( transliteration of seoul road ) twenty - five koreans who sought refuge arrived at seoul international airport yesterday and began to live a new life in korea .
they then waved to the korean television camera .
li song , a 43 - year - old factory worker , said at a press conference at the airport : " we want to settle here and live in a free and promising world . "
another man said : " as south korea is a free country , i did not hesitate to die here . "
last thursday , these koreans intruded into the spanish embassy in beijing and resolutely declared their intention to go to the rok .
on friday , china allowed them to go to seoul via the philippines .
they came from six families and two of them had no parents .
they were the largest group of people fleeing since the korean war ended .
according to seoul 's national intelligence agency , these people will join the 2,000 koreans who have settled down in south korea , of which 138 will seek refuge with south korea this year .
last year , 583 people rushed to korea to break the record .
the newly arrived 25 will be adapted to study in a government refuge near seoul .
the primary objective of the course is to assist the transformer to overcome the stress of fleeing and then to receive counselling in order to adapt to korean culture , including understanding capitalism .
the final step is to receive new work training .
