cheney fails in middle east visit : gulf daily
( agence france - presse , dubai ) - the gulf countries press said on monday that u . s . vice president cheney 's middle east visit failed .
cheney 's visit was to persuade middle east countries to support us attacks on iraq .
cheney went to kuwait monday after visiting all the gulf countries , but even the united states ' most loyal allies are opposed to attacking baghdad .
the salem arab newspaper said , " what the vice president heard was that the united states must stop israeli terrorist activities and prevent israel from possessing weapons of mass destruction . "
the paper also pointed out : " if the united states continues not considering the interests of middle east countries , it will lose its interests in the gulf region . "
the uae gulf daily also said : " this is a new failure of the united states in the middle east after it has run into snags in europe .
most of the us european allies are openly opposed to the attack on iraq . "
cheney denied in bahrain yesterday that his middle east trip was aimed at organizing military strikes against iraq .
at a joint press conference with bahrain 's crown prince sahman , he said he denied that some people believed that the only thing he was interested in during his trip was organizing a military attack on iraq .
cheney said that he and crown prince sahman mainly discussed the war on terrorism , the latest developments in the middle east , and the situation in afghanistan .
cheney arrived in israel on monday evening for a visit . it is expected that he will meet with israeli prime minister ehud olmert to discuss the latest developments in the israeli - palestinian situation .
on the other hand , israeli and palestinian commanders in the war zones in the west bank and the qassam zone unexpectedly held talks yesterday with a view to stopping violent activities in the region .
this meeting was probably the first step that israel took in withdrawing its troops from palestinian - controlled areas .
