more police patrol on streets in britain
( united states , london ) the british government is committed to solving the increasingly serious street crime problem and will deploy more policemen to patrol the scene .
interior minister blunkett said that it is very necessary to curb rising street robberies and violence and to send additional police to step up patrol .
he said : " we indeed should rectify the order on the streets because law - abiding citizens hope to travel safely on the streets and live a safe life . there is no need to fear that they will be attacked . "
although the overall crime rate in britain has decreased , there has been a 13 percent increase in street crimes between 2000 and 2001 .
the situation in london was even more shocking : in september and november alone , 13,248 robberies were reported , more than double the figure of 8,814 cases in the same period of the previous year .
the government also said that the increase in crimes was mainly due to the increase in the number of mobile phone robberies . last year , more than 700,000 mobile phone robberies occurred nationwide .
this was the first time that british police focused their crackdown on street hooligans and robberies and previously concentrated their efforts on cracking down on illegal possession of firearms and on selling of drugs on the streets .
the new plan will be implemented first in 10 streets where crimes are concentrated .
police will step up patrols in these streets and provide more protection to victims .
workers from 10 state - owned factories in liaoning hold demonstrations
workers from 10 state - owned factories in liaoyang , northeast china 's liaoning province staged a collective demonstration yesterday in protest against arrears of wages and pensions , low compensation fees , and corruption .
at the same time , the demonstration of dismissed oil workers in daqing in heilongjiang province has been going on for three weeks .
the hong kong - based china human rights movement information center said that liaoyang city 's public security bureau arrested a 54 - year - old yao fuxin , the organizer of the demonstration and also arrested more than 10 other workers who organized demonstrations .
yao 's relative , who declined to reveal his name , said : " when he went out to buy something , he did not come back . several people saw him taken away . "
in addition , in daqing oilfield , which is close to heilongjiang province , the police and the daqing petroleum administration told reporters that the sit - in demonstration by dismissed oil workers has entered its third week , but the number of workers participating in the sit - in has dropped from 50,000 to over 1,000 .
it is reported that workers in these two cities have set up independent trade unions and have decided to negotiate through elections .
according to law , such actions are not permitted .
han dong - fang , the host of the china workers ' movement organization based in hong kong , said : although the two demonstrations have just ended , the problem has actually existed for a long time .
han also said demonstrations also took place in a textile factory in guangyuan city , sichuan on monday . several workers who organized the weekend strike were arrested . as a result , 1,000 workers held demonstrations in protest .
singapore airlines ' air accident investigation committee delays prosecutors ' suspicion
( taipei news ) the singapore airlines air crash accident has been going on for one and a half years , but the report on the air crash investigation report of the taiwan flight safety council has been delayed again and again , with the result that the taoyuan air inspection agency 's investigation operation has stagnated . the prosecutor 's office has questioned some myths in the accident and the flight safety council has promised to submit the investigation report in april .
at 11 : 18 p.m . on october 31 , 2000 , a singaporean airline flight from chiang kai - shek airport to los angeles , collided with the right runway , collided with two excavators on the runway , causing the explosion , killing 83 passengers and injuring nearly 100 .
the chung - kuo shih - pao reported yesterday that the taoyuan prefectural investigation bureau , which is responsible for investigating the criminal suspect after the air crash , had several disputes over its investigation rights with the flying an investigation unit .
since the air crash , wang tiansheng , procurator general of the taoyuan prefectural investigation and prosecution bureau , has been promoted to be the procurator general of taichung , chen shouhuang has been replaced , and huang chih - hsin , the prosecutor in charge of the case , has also been transferred to the north inspection , and the case has been taken over by jiangyuan .
the flight safety council had originally indicated that the investigation report could be completed by the end of last year and then postponed to the end of january . after the change was completed in february , there was still no follow - up report . with the prosecution 's urging , the air safety council promised to deliver the report in april .
since the pz - 006 flight ends in los angeles , families of some of the victims have already brought a huge amount of civil compensation to the us court , requesting compensation from singapore airlines as well as taiwan civil aviation authority .
the claim made by the families of the victims is tantamount to accusing taiwan 's control tower of being held responsible for negligence . therefore , the investigation conclusions of the taoyuan prefectural inspection department are particularly eye - catching .
