global warming warns of collapse of ice in antarctic
( auckland ) experts from the us national ice and snow data center said yesterday that an ice cap on the antarctic has been totally disintegrated and has been split into several thousand iceberg . this is the largest of such incidents in the past 30 years , thus again sounding an alarm on the issue of global warming .
it is reported that an ice sheets of the larson b ice , measuring 3,250 square kilometers , near the eastern coast of south polar island , has been totally disintegrated within 35 days .
the center warned that with the arrival of the hot summer , other ice sheets are also on the verge of collapse .
this indicates that the flow of ice in southern sahara will increase , and the sea level will rise and cause harm to the low - altitude areas .
the center at colorado university said on its website ( nidcorg . org ) that there might have been 10,000 - ton larson - b ice weighing 720 - million tonnes in 2000 , which started to split up on 31 january this year and caused several thousand shrapes of ice to form in the sea of wedro .
the center also said that the cause of the ice cap split was the warming of the region .
