( agence france - presse , london ) - results of a poll released yesterday show that more than half of british voters do not support u . s . government 's support of u . s . attack on iraq .
a poll conducted by the guardian and the opinion poll agencies showed that 51 percent of voters opposed the us attack on iraq .
this is contrary to similar polls conducted last year and three years ago when most british voters supported attacking iraq .
similar opinion polls published by the us cable news network and time magazine the day before yesterday showed that 70 percent of americans support the government 's attack on iraq to overthrow the woo regime .
in ottawa , canadian prime minister chretien said the day before yesterday that canada would consider joining if us - led coalition forces attack iraq .
chretien and other canadian ministers have all along been uneasy about bush 's tough stance toward iraq 's sonny doo and has always insisted that there is no evidence to show that he has links with qatar .
however , chretien seems to have changed his original stance after holding talks with bush in washington last thursday .
he told cbs television that he would seriously consider any request from the united states for military assistance outside afghanistan .
