( transliteration ) us defense department officials said on monday that the bush administration had decided to lower the alert level of air force fighters patrolling since the september 11 attacks , but would still maintain fewer patrol missions and allow aircraft to await orders on the runway .
the defense department said the continuous flying night and night had cost the air force 500 - million dollars ( about 900 - million singapore dollars ) , but air patrols over washington would continue . air patrols in the new york area will be suspended apart from occasional emergency situations .
the decision to reduce or stop air patrol was made by the airport and airlines after the september 11 incident .
defense ministry spokesman clark told reporters : " we are studying a plan in various ways , including carrying out fighter patrol over a designated area , carrying out temporary decision - making patrols on the damaged fighter planes , and taking stand - by measures on runway of different levels . "
the runway is ready to take off at any time .
she also said that alert will be adjusted at any time according to the level of threat .
