( pyongyang , seoul ) the sand storms that have just swept northern china yesterday fiercely attacked the korean peninsula , including the capital of the democratic people 's republic of korea ( dprk ) pyongyang and the capital of seoul of the republic of korea ( rok ) .
according to a xinhua news agency report , a strong sand storm hit pyongyang early yesterday morning .
from the early morning , the entire pyongyang area has been covered with grey dust .
this is the first sandstorm that the dprk has experienced since spring this year .
six routes suspended
according to another report by the beijing people 's network , a large area of " sandstorms " occurred in the rok yesterday . six domestic flights were suspended except the inchon international airport .
sandstorms occurred across the country in south korea .
tests by the rok environment ministry showed that the amount of minor dust in the sky of seoul yesterday afternoon exceeded the normal level of 17 times , reaching 1,000 micrograms per cubic meter , the highest in history .
affected by the dust weather throughout the country , south korea , apart from the inchuan international airport , has maintained its normal operation . six domestic flights , including daqiu , weishan and pu , have been suspended , and passengers on more than 30 flights have switched to other transport means .
in addition , according to an associated press report , the south korean government yesterday ordered kindergartens and primary schools across the country to temporarily suspend classes to prevent their children from being polluted by the air .
three dust storms have occurred in seoul , south korea so far this year .
the south korean meteorological agency forecast yesterday that " the strong rising air currents that have occurred in desert areas such as china and mongolia spread over the sky over northern china and passed through south korea by northwest wind " .
it is enough to destroy medium - sized planets by colliding with the earth .
( florida , united states ) a small planet can destroy a medium - sized city but it was not discovered in advance within 460,000 km of the earth . astronomers only learned of this four days later .
astronomers find it difficult to detect the small planet , measuring about 50 meters in diameter from the sun .
the small planet passed the earth on march 8 , but it is far away by march 12 when it is discovered .
williams , who is located at the international astronomical association center in cambridge , massachusetts , has helped determine the azimuth .
from the perspective of astronomy , the planet is very close to the earth because the moon is 400,000 km away from the earth .
williams told florida 's " today daily " on wednesday , " the key is that the satellite should be detected before it is issued from the sun . "
only in this way will astronomers be able to determine the orbit of the asteroids and predict whether it will impact the earth .
when a large and almost small star hit the earth in 1908 , it crashed a 32 - kilometer wide pit in siberia 's forest .
