illegally acquiring state secrets and offering bribes to chinese american engineers , sentenced to five years ' imprisonment
beijing 's no . 1 intermediate people 's court yesterday sentenced american chinese engineer fang fuming to five years ' imprisonment on charges of illegally obtaining state secrets and offering a bribe on behalf of a company .
the case drew protests from the united states .
a spokesperson for the us embassy in china said that fang fuming will be expelled after the prison term expires .
the prison term will be adjusted according to the duration of his imprisonment .
the us embassy had sent a diplomat to hear the hearing .
fang fuming 's lawyer said that his clients had been in jail for two years , but china said they had not been so long .
xinhua news agency confirmed the verdict .
it said that from 1995 to 1999 , fang fuming received 35 documents containing state secrets and bribed chinese civil servants with 245,000 us dollars ( about 45,000 singapore dollars ) to assist foreign investors in bidding for china 's power projects .
fang fuming is an electrical engineering consultant for foreign companies in china and other parts of asia .
fang fuming 's lawyer cohen said that fang fuming denied offering a bribe , claiming that he was the victim of a corrupt chinese power official .
fang fuming used to be a chinese power official and a us citizen in 1994 .
in the past two years , a number of us citizens and residents have been charged with violating china 's national security law .
fang fuming was once detained , causing tensions in sino - us relations .
the us government has time and again protested against china 's handling of the fang chong - ming case , saying that the authorities have not violated international standards by holding trial for several months now and again .
fang fuming 's family said that he was treated badly .
his wife and two children are american citizens .
cohen said : the two sides have been detained on 28 february 2000 . however , the detention period proposed by the chinese foreign ministry is 28 august 2000 .
china does not want to confirm whether hu jintao will visit the united states as planned
( beijing comprehensive ) the warming - up of sino - us relations , which had once been warming up due to us president bush 's visit to china , yesterday confirmed abolishing the plan for the visit of a naval task force to the united states this year and refused to determine whether state vice president hu jintao will visit the united states as scheduled .
in answering a question at a regular news conference , foreign ministry spokeswoman zhang qiyue said : " as far as i know , the chinese naval task group is preparing to visit foreign countries as planned . their plans do not include the us ports . "
when a reporter asked twice whether hu jintao 's plan to visit the united states was affected or not , she asked to clarify whether an earlier reply could be interpreted as that hu jintao 's visit to the united states would be carried out as scheduled in april , zhang qiyue was unwilling to make more comments or confirmed .
zhang qiyue only repeatedly criticized the us side for " doing a series of things in violation of the three sino - us joint communiques " in a short period of one month after bush 's visit to china , and demanded that the us side " stop using the taiwan issue to interfere in china 's internal affairs . "
on the other hand , in washington , it is not appropriate for the united states to ignore china 's warnings that sino - us relations are experiencing a " cold wind " and insist on allowing taiwan 's defense secretary to attend the " us - taiwan defense summit " in florida .
beijing has time and again attacked us defense secretary tang yao - ming for issuing a visa to taiwan earlier this month .
tang yao - ming also met with two us senior officials at that time .
state department spokesman richard boucher was questioned by reporters at the regular news conference by reporters on china 's complaints on this matter , but he clearly tried his utmost to avoid launching a verbal war with china .
he said : " our stand after the talks is known to all .
if you ask me about this everyday , i would like to explain it everyday . china wants to ask this question everyday , and we want to explain it everyday . "
he said : " our position remains unchanged . these are normal contacts between us and the people of taiwan . we will continue to do so . "
zhang qiyue also confirmed russian media reports yesterday that at russian president putin 's request , chinese state president jiang zemin talked with him over the phone the night before . the two sides mainly exchanged views on the issue of mutually beneficial cooperation between china and russia .
both sides held that the mutually beneficial cooperation between china and russia conforms to the interests of the two countries and the two peoples .
